 "last_comment_author": "Covfefebrulee", "is_video": false, "video_link": "", "is_new_user": false, "domain": "twitter-thread.com", "is_crosspost": false, "preview": "https://media.scored.co/preview/1ASZR8gSHQ.png", "removal_source": "", "link": "https://twitter-thread.com/t/2045574398573453312", "author_flair_class": "", "is_removed": false, "media": {"resized_resolutions": [], "blurhash": "", "full_resolution": []}, "title": "Palantir just published their political manifesto. It's the most important thread you'll read today.", "last_comment_created": 1776630707605, "content": "", "score_down": 0, "author_flair_text": "", "pro_tier": 0, "is_stickied": false, "is_nsfw": false, "is_deleted": false, "is_image": false, "comments": 23, "score_up": 18, "is_edited": false, "is_moderator": false, "awards": 0, "vote_state": 2, "link_metadata": {"description": "Because we get asked a lot.The Technological Republic, in brief.1. Silicon Valley owes a moral debt to the country that made its rise possible. The engineering elite of Silicon Valley has an affirmative obligation to participate in the defense of the nation.2. We must rebel against the tyranny of the apps. Is the iPhone our greatest creative if not crowning achievement as a civilization? The object has changed our lives, but it may also now be limiting and constraining our sense of the possible.3. Free email is not enough. The decadence of a culture or civilization, and indeed its ruling class, will be forgiven only if that culture is capable of delivering economic growth and security for the public.4. The limits of soft power, of soaring rhetoric alone, have been exposed. The ability of free and democratic societies to prevail requires something more than moral appeal. It requires hard power, and hard power in this century will be built on software.5. The question is not whether A.I. weapons will be built; ", "title": "Because we get asked a lot. by @PalantirTech(Palantir) | Twitter Thread Reader"}, "post_flair_text"